  <rdfs:comment rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Adult onset Still's disease (AoSD) is a rare form of inflammatory arthritis that affects the entire body, impacting joints and organs. Typically affecting individuals over the age of 16, patients often endure bouts of elevated fever, joint discomfort, and skin rash. Blood tests commonly indicate elevated white blood cell counts. Despite extensive research, the exact cause of AoSD remains elusive, with uncertainty over whether it stems from autoimmune or autoinflammatory origins. The disease's progression varies widely among patients; while some experience sudden onset followed by swift and complete recovery, others contend with chronic manifestations or symptom flare-ups alternating with periods of remission. AoSD bears a resemblance to systemic juvenile rheumatoid arthritis, differing primarily in the age of onset. Although a definitive cure remains elusive, treatment options exist to manage inflammation and mitigate potential organ damage. There are three main patterns of the clinical course of AoSD namely monophasic, intermittent, and chronic. There is an approximately equal distribution in each category however some studies have shown a chronic articular pattern to be more common.</rdfs:comment>
  <ARI_Synonym rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Adult Still's disease</ARI_Synonym>
  <ARI_DefSource rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Mitrovic 2019; https://link.springer.com/chapter/10.1007/978-3-030-19055-2_6</ARI_DefSource>
  <evidenceQuality rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Antibody</evidenceQuality>
  <diseaseCategory rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Autoimmune</diseaseCategory>
  <ARI_Version rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">2</ARI_Version>
  <prevalencePer100k rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#decimal">14711.0</prevalencePer100k>
  <ARI_PrevalenceDesc rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Female 9271/100k; Male 5440/100k; F:M ratio 1.70423</ARI_PrevalenceDesc>
  <ageRange rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">20-45 years</ageRange>
  <ARI_RefLink rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Adult Onset Still’s Disease Support Group | https://www.facebook.com/groups/22056595992/</ARI_RefLink>
  <ARI_RefLink rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Living with an Invisible Disease | https://www.sobi.com/en/stories/living-invisible-disease</ARI_RefLink>
  <ARI_RefLink rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Not Standing Still's Disease | https://www.notstandingstillsdisease.com/</ARI_RefLink>
  <ARI_RefLink rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Arthritis Foundation | http://www.arthritis.org/</ARI_RefLink>
  <ARI_RefLink rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">International Still's Disease Foundation | http://www.stillsdisease.org/</ARI_RefLink>
  <ARI_RefLink rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Surviving Stills: Amy’s Story | https://versusarthritis.org/news/2020/november/surviving-still-s-amy-s-story/</ARI_RefLink>
  <ARI_RefLink rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Link to Healthline | https://www.healthline.com/health/adult-stills-disease</ARI_RefLink>
  <ARI_RefLink rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Link to Cleveland Clinic | https://my.clevelandclinic.org/health/diseases/adult-onset-stills-disease-aosd</ARI_RefLink>
  <ARI_ClinicalSubtype rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Chronic Articular AOSD - Persistent arthritis as the dominant feature.</ARI_ClinicalSubtype>
  <ARI_ClinicalSubtype rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Systemic AOSD - Severe inflammation with high fever, rash, and organ involvement.</ARI_ClinicalSubtype>
  <ARI_ClinicalSubtype rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Monophasic AOSD - A single episode that resolves completely.</ARI_ClinicalSubtype>
  <ARI_ClinicalSubtype rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Intermittent AOSD - Recurring episodes with symptom-free periods.</ARI_ClinicalSubtype>
  <ARI_Author rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Emily Romanello | https://www.linkedin.com/in/emily-romanello-1392432a</ARI_Author>
  <ARI_AuthorDate rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">2024-09</ARI_AuthorDate>
  <ARI_SurveyCode rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">AOSD</ARI_SurveyCode>
  <ARI_ChangeLog rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">2026-06-15 10:37 | Importer | Imported from ARI core reports</ARI_ChangeLog>
</owl:NamedIndividual>

