  <rdfs:label rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Chronic multifocal osteomyelitis</rdfs:label>
  <ARI_Obsolete rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">false</ARI_Obsolete>
  <ARI_ID rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">ARI:0001066</ARI_ID>
  <ARI_SNOMED rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">240151005</ARI_SNOMED>
  <ARI_DOID rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">0060645</ARI_DOID>
  <ARI_ICD10 rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">M86.3</ARI_ICD10>
  <ARI_MESH rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">C535456</ARI_MESH>
  <ARI_OMOP rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">4344376</ARI_OMOP>
  <ARI_DXCODE rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">240151005</ARI_DXCODE>
  <rdfs:comment rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Chronic multifocal osteomyelitis (CRMO) occurs due to an immune system attack on the bones, which has not yet been deemed autoimmune or autoinflammatory in nature, which causes periodic episodes of inflammation of the bones. CRMO is a non bacterial type of osteomyelitis that is considered when bacterial options have been ruled out.

CRMO most commonly affects the long bones as well as the pelvis or spine. This disease can also be diagnosed along with inflammatory bowel disease or psoriasis. CRMO usually occurs in children and can cause bone deformities or slow growth in children. Although there is no cure for CRMO, treatments involved medications such as non-steroidal anti-inflammatory medications, antirheumatic drugs, biologics, and more.

Chronic non-bacterial osteomyelitis (CNO) is a rare auto-inflammatory bone disorder with a prevalence of around one in a million patients. In the more severe form, it is referred to as chronic recurrent multifocal osteomyelitis (CRMO).</rdfs:comment>
  <ARI_DefSource rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Buch 2018; https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/30456556/</ARI_DefSource>
  <ARI_Pubmed rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/30456556/</ARI_Pubmed>
  <evidenceQuality rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Unconfirmed</evidenceQuality>
  <diseaseCategory rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Unconfirmed</diseaseCategory>
  <ARI_Version rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">2</ARI_Version>
  <ageRange rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">9-10 years</ageRange>
  <ARI_ClinicalSubtype rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">CRMO, Nonbacterial - Chronic bone inflammation without infection.</ARI_ClinicalSubtype>
  <ARI_Author rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Autoimmune Registry</ARI_Author>
