  <rdfs:comment rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Felty syndrome is a rare, potentially serious disorder which is characterized by the presence of three symptoms: rheumatoid arthritis, splenomegaly (enlarged spleen) and neutropenia (a decreased white cell count) which can lead to repeated infections.  It also associated with rheumatoid factor (RF) positive rheumatoid arthritis.</rdfs:comment>
  <ARI_Synonym rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">FS</ARI_Synonym>
