  <hasSymptom rdf:resource="#Sym_0001140_1327"/>
  <rdfs:label rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Necrotizing vasculitis</rdfs:label>
  <ARI_Obsolete rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">false</ARI_Obsolete>
  <ARI_ID rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">ARI:0001140</ARI_ID>
  <ARI_SNOMED rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">11791001</ARI_SNOMED>
  <ARI_OMOP rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">4039691</ARI_OMOP>
  <ARI_DXCODE rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">11791001</ARI_DXCODE>
  <rdfs:comment rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Vasculitis is an inflammation of blood vessels. When vasculitis is severe, blood cannot reach important organs or tissues. In severe cases, the tissue dies, which is called necrosis, and the term "necrotizing vasculitis" is used. It is also called "systemic vasculitis" since the severity of the disease can be widespread. 

Necrotizing vasculitis can lead to blood clots, weight loss, loss of weight, exhaustion, depression, fever, and widespread pain that worsens in the morning.
The specific location of vasculitis inflammation determines what tissue or organs (e.g., kidneys, fingers, head) are affected, and the type of vasculitis often depends on the location.  For more information, see the specific forms of vasculitis elsewhere on the website (listed above).</rdfs:comment>
  <ARI_DefSource rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Arora 2014; https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4252802/</ARI_DefSource>
  <evidenceQuality rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Immune-mediated</evidenceQuality>
  <diseaseCategory rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Autoimmune</diseaseCategory>
  <ARI_Version rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">2</ARI_Version>
  <prevalencePer100k rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#decimal">20227.0</prevalencePer100k>
  <ARI_PrevalenceDesc rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Female 14940/100k; Male 5286/100k; F:M ratio 2.82633</ARI_PrevalenceDesc>
  <ageRange rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">50-70 years</ageRange>
  <ARI_RefLink rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Link to Healthline | https://www.healthline.com/health/necrotizing-vasculitis</ARI_RefLink>
  <ARI_ClinicalSubtype rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Necrotizing Vasculitis, Small Vessel - Involves capillaries and small arteries.</ARI_ClinicalSubtype>
  <ARI_ClinicalSubtype rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Necrotizing Vasculitis, Medium Vessel - Affects medium-sized arteries.</ARI_ClinicalSubtype>
  <ARI_Author rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Autoimmune Registry</ARI_Author>
  <ARI_AuthorDate rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">2024-09</ARI_AuthorDate>
  <ARI_SurveyCode rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">NV</ARI_SurveyCode>
  <ARI_ChangeLog rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">2026-06-15 10:37 | Importer | Imported from ARI core reports</ARI_ChangeLog>
