  <rdfs:comment rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Polyarteritis nodosa is an autoimmune disease that causes damage, weakness, and swelling to arteries. Small and medium-sized arteritis are affected by this disease. The autoimmune response that causes PAN is commonly triggered by drugs, vaccines, and both viral and bacterial infections.  PAN is a multisystem disorder, so any organ in the body can be affected. Typically, the skin, heart, peripheral nervous system, kidneys, joints, eyes, and gastrointestinal system are affected. Common symptoms include feelings of malaise, pain, and skin irritation.  There is no cure for PAN, but there are treatments to help with symptoms and disease progression. Outcomes vary depending on symptoms and disease severity, and relapses are possible.  If left untreated, some complications may be fatal.</rdfs:comment>
  <ARI_Synonym rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Classic polyarteritis nodosa</ARI_Synonym>
  <ARI_Synonym rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">c-PAN</ARI_Synonym>
  <ARI_Synonym rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Periarteritis nodosa</ARI_Synonym>
  <ARI_Synonym rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Polyarteritis</ARI_Synonym>
  <ARI_Synonym rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">PAN</ARI_Synonym>
  <ARI_DefSource rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Hernández-Rodríguez 2014; https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/24485157/</ARI_DefSource>
  <ARI_Pubmed rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/24485157/</ARI_Pubmed>
  <evidenceQuality rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Unconfirmed</evidenceQuality>
  <diseaseCategory rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Unconfirmed</diseaseCategory>
  <ARI_Version rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">2</ARI_Version>
  <prevalencePer100k rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#decimal">26127.0</prevalencePer100k>
  <ARI_PrevalenceDesc rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Female 15477/100k; Male 10650/100k; F:M ratio 1.45324</ARI_PrevalenceDesc>
  <ageRange rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">50-70 years</ageRange>
  <ARI_RefLink rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Vaculitis Foundation | https://www.vasculitisfoundation.org/</ARI_RefLink>
  <ARI_RefLink rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">PAN - Polyarteritis Nodosa | https://www.facebook.com/groups/6799967156</ARI_RefLink>
  <ARI_RefLink rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Link to Cleveland Clinic | https://my.clevelandclinic.org/health/diseases/polyarteritis-nodosa-pan</ARI_RefLink>
  <ARI_RefLink rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Link to Healthline | https://www.healthline.com/health/polyarteritis-nodosa</ARI_RefLink>
  <ARI_RefLink rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Vasculitis Foundation Canada | https://vasculitis.ca/</ARI_RefLink>
  <ARI_ClinicalSubtype rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">PAN, Classic - Medium-vessel vasculitis affecting multiple organs.</ARI_ClinicalSubtype>
  <ARI_ClinicalSubtype rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">PAN, Hepatitis B-Associated - Linked to HBV infection.</ARI_ClinicalSubtype>
