  <rdfs:comment rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Polymyalgia rheumatica (PMR) is an autoimmune disease that causes an inflammatory reaction affecting the lining of joints, especially the shoulders and hips, and sometimes the arteries and some major branches of the aorta. It is usually associated with temporal arteritis.</rdfs:comment>
  <ARI_DefSource rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Crowson 2017; https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5623160/</ARI_DefSource>
