  <rdfs:comment rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">PSC is a rare progressive disorder of the liver which is characterized by inflammation, thickening, and abnormal formation of fibrous tissue within the passages that carry bile from the liver (bile ducts). Both bile ducts within the liver and outside the liver are affected.</rdfs:comment>
