  <rdfs:comment rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">SLE, the most common type of lupus, is a chronic inflammatory disease that occurs when the body's immune system attacks its own tissues and organs. Inflammation caused by lupus can affect many different body systems — including joints, skin, kidneys, blood cells, brain, heart and lungs.</rdfs:comment>
